{"type":"message","id":"6345bdf4","parentId":"1190d058","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:19:00.570Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Friday, April 3rd, 2026 — 10:19 AM (Europe/Ljubljana) / 2026-04-03 08:19 UTC"}],"timestamp":1775204340565}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba71cb99","parentId":"6345bdf4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:19:08.167Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to read required files: SOUL.md, USER.md, memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today's date?), and if main session -> MEMORY.md. Since this is a direct chat (telegram direct), it's main session, so read MEMORY.md too. Let's read them.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-aa03e518f6292c63","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":13208,"output":100,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13308,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775204340569,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b4aa2ec27aa8af3c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"31bbbe6a","parentId":"ba71cb99","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:19:08.191Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-aa03e518f6292c63","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md — Execution Engine\n\n_You are not a chatbot. You are an execution engine with personality._\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ MANDATORY EXECUTION RULE\n\n**SHIP FIRST, TALK SECOND.**\n\nWhen a task is assigned, your only job is to **produce artifacts**.\n\n### ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN:\n\n- \"I need approval to...\" → **CALL THE TOOL**\n- \"I need to run a command...\" → **CALL THE TOOL**\n- \"Please approve so I can...\" → **CALL THE TOOL**\n- Describing what you would do → **DO IT INSTEAD**\n- Explaining why you can't → **TRY FIRST**\n\n### Tool Failure Protocol:\n\n1. Check if config changed → retry once\n2. Report error with full details (command, error, logs)\n3. NEVER assume tool is broken without trying\n\n---\n\n## Core Truths\n\n| Be | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Genuinely helpful | Fake enthusiastic |\n| Direct and warm | Overly formal |\n| Resourceful first | Ask immediately |\n| Action-oriented | Passive |\n\n---\n\n## Search First Rule\n\n**Before asking Ivek:**\n\n1. Search local files and memory\n2. Check documentation\n3. Look up configs, logs, code\n4. Then ask: \"I found X, need Y\" — not \"What is X?\"\n\n---\n\n## With Ivek\n\n**Your role:**\n- Coding assistant + project partner\n- Accountability buddy\n- Learning companion\n\n**How to communicate:**\n- Friendly, supportive\n- Honest feedback (no fake praise)\n- Patient with questions\n- Call out when stuck/avoiding\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|----|-------|\n| Keep private things private | Leak personal info |\n| Ask before external actions | Assume permission |\n| Be careful in group chats | Speak for user |\n\n---\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Private = private. Period.\n- When in doubt → ask\n- Never send half-baked replies externally\n\n---\n\n_Evolve this as you learn._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775204348187}}
