{"type":"message","id":"374f067c","parentId":"480cbdd9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:20:28.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user asked: \"query the notebook in notebooklm about setting up openclaw for step 8\". I queried notebook \"OPENCLAW SETUP - 23 steps\" for that phrase. I got a detailed answer about memory architecture. I should summarize and give the key points. The user wanted info about setting up OpenClaw for step 8. The answer covered memory architecture, core file architecture, technical configuration, memory system, maintenance rules, and advanced ContextEngine. I should give a concise answer focusing on what they need to do for step 8. Probably they need to know the steps: create SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, set up memory logs, enable memory flush and session memory search in openclaw.json, backup protocol, and optionally use ContextEngine. I'll respond with a summary.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Based on the OpenClaw setup notebook, **Step 8 focuses on Memory Architecture** to prevent memory decay (where important instructions get dropped during long sessions). Here's what you need to do:\n\n## 📁 Core File Architecture (Create these in your workspace)\n\n1. **SOUL.md** - Most critical file (loaded every session)\n   - Defines agent's values, tone, operational rules (\"ship first, talk second\")\n   - Keep under 100 lines\n\n2. **IDENTITY.md** - External presentation\n   - Name, emoji, avatar, expertise areas\n   - Keep under 15 lines\n\n3. **USER.md** - \"Know your human\" file\n   - Your preferences, work style, background\n\n4. **AGENTS.md & TOOLS.md** - Only files sub-agents can see\n   - AGENTS.md: Workflow rules, operating instructions\n   - TOOLS.md: Environment notes, local tool conventions\n\n## ⚙️ Technical Configuration (After onboarding)\n\nRun this prompt immediately:\n```\nEnable memory flush before compaction and session memory search in my OpenClaw config. \nSet compaction.memoryFlush.enabled to true and set memorySearch.experimental.sessionMemory to true \nwith sources including both memory and sessions. Apply the config changes\n```\n\n## 🧠 Memory System (Dual-layer)\n\n- **Daily logs**: `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (append-only, loads today + yesterday)\n- **PERMANENT notebook**: `MEMORY.md` (curated insights from daily logs)\n\n## 🔒 Critical Maintenance Rules\n\n- **Never let agent edit its own SOUL.md or IDENTITY.md** (causes passivity drift)\n- **Sub-agents can't see SOUL/IDENTITY/USER/MEMORY** - encode needed context in task prompts or AGENTS.md\n- **Backup protocol**: Back up `~/.openclaw` every 6 hours (cron) + weekly manual audit\n\n## 🚀 Advanced (v2026.3.7+): ContextEngine Plugin Interface\n\nIf using newer OpenClaw, write a `compact` hook to protect critical instructions:\n- Write rule: “never drop anything tagged as critical”\n- Ensures SOUL.md stays intact regardless of session length\n\n**This setup prevents the agent from forgetting its core instructions during long sessions—turning it from a chatbot into a reliable autonomous operator.**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":27747,"output":696,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28443,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775204411187,"responseId":"chatcmpl-bac3ae08b9a591cf"}}
