{"type":"message","id":"8f3ddd12","parentId":"5ff180b0","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:27:30.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to verify steps are completed and set up context engine. We have verified step 8 (memory flush enabled). Now need to set up context engine. From the notebook, context engine is available in v2026.3.7+. We have OpenClaw 2026.4.1, so it should be available. However, the hooks list didn't show a context-engine hook. Maybe it's not installed by default; we might need to enable it via config or install a hook pack. Let's check if there's a context engine plugin or hook. We can look for \"context\" in plugins list. I saw none. Let's search for context engine in the skills or docs. We can also check if there's a way to enable it via openclaw config. Let's try to see if there's a context-engine hook pack available. We can try to install it via openclaw plugins install. But first, let's check the current config for any context engine settings. We can read the openclaw.json again and see if there's a contextEngine section. We already have compaction and memorySearch. Maybe we need to add contextEngine.enabled: true. Let's check the docs quickly via web search? But we can also try to see if there's a hook for context engine in the plugin list under a different name. Let's grep for \"context\" in the plugin list output (we have it). We can run a command to get the plugin list in JSON and search. But easier: let's just try to enable context engine via config. We'll update openclaw.json to include contextEngine: { enabled: true }. Then we can check if hooks appear. Let's do that.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-89d6da726a039e0b","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/.openclaw/openclaw.json","edits":[{"oldText":"{\n  \"compaction\": {\n    \"memoryFlush\": {\n      \"enabled\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"memorySearch\": {\n    \"experimental\": {\n      \"sessionMemory\": true\n    }\n  }\n}","newText":"{\n  \"compaction\": {\n    \"memoryFlush\": {\n      \"enabled\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"memorySearch\": {\n    \"experimental\": {\n      \"sessionMemory\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"contextEngine\": {\n    \"enabled\": true\n  }\n}"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":38089,"output":552,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38641,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775204833286,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9b321e1976931d40"}}
