{"type":"message","id":"d24de4f7","parentId":"4488fd3e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:27:44.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have completed Step 8 (memory architecture) and enabled Context Engine. The openclaw.json is updated. What would you like to do next?\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"✅ Step 8 completed: Memory flush and session memory search enabled.\n✅ Context Engine enabled in openclaw.json.\n\nAll memory architecture steps are done. Your agent now has persistent memory and Context Engine active. What's next?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":38443,"output":84,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38527,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775204858241,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9ce4a5e9d79b6737"}}
{"type":"message","id":"edddf9fd","parentId":"d24de4f7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:28:34.792Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1244\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6735239700\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ivek\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-03 10:28 GMT+2\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ivek (6735239700)\",\n  \"id\": \"6735239700\",\n  \"name\": \"Ivek\"\n}\n```\n\nwhat did you do the enable contextengine and what function does it have"}],"timestamp":1775204914786}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b15a7fc","parentId":"edddf9fd","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:28:47.305Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We enabled Context Engine by adding `\"contextEngine\": { \"enabled\": true }` to openclaw.json. It controls the memory pipeline via hooks (ingest, assemble, compact, afterTurn, prepareSubagentSpawn) to prevent memory decay and customize how context is processed.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I enabled Context Engine by adding `\"contextEngine\": { \"enabled\": true }` to your `openclaw.json`.\n\n**What it does:**  \nContext Engine gives you six lifecycle hooks to fully control OpenClaw's memory pipeline:\n- **bootstrap**: Load external data when agent starts\n- **ingest**: Filter/tag/prioritize new context\n- **assemble**: Control how context is built for LLM (custom RAG)\n- **compact**: Decide what stays/goes during compression (you can tag SOUL.md as critical to never drop it)\n- **afterTurn**: Log/analyze/learn after each response\n- **prepareSubagentSpawn**: Set up isolated memory for sub-agents\n\nThis solves the memory decay problem by letting you explicitly protect critical instructions (like SOUL.md) from being compacted away, and customize how your agent processes and retains information."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":38655,"output":245,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38900,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775204914790,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8f7e6f58143b029c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"96be88f5","parentId":"9b15a7fc","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:30:49.967Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1246\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6735239700\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ivek\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-03 10:30 GMT+2\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ivek (6735239700)\",\n  \"id\": \"6735239700\",\n  \"name\": \"Ivek\"\n}\n```\n\nhow will this affect my use of openclaw"}],"timestamp":1775205049961}}
{"type":"message","id":"d88a9883","parentId":"96be88f5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:31:09.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to answer how enabling Context Engine affects use of OpenClaw. Provide concise answer.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"With Context Engine enabled, your OpenClaw agent gains fine‑grained control over how memory is processed:\n\n1. **No more silent loss of core instructions** – you can tag `SOUL.md` (or any critical text) as “critical” in the `compact` hook, guaranteeing it never gets dropped during session compaction, no matter how long the conversation grows.\n\n2. **Custom knowledge injection** – via the `bootstrap` and `ingest` hooks you can automatically load external data (e.g., your Notion DB, personal notes, or FAQs) every time the agent starts or new context arrives.\n\n3. **Tailored context assembly** – the `assemble` hook lets you run a custom RAG pipeline, so the agent retrieves only the most relevant snippets from your knowledge base before each response.\n\n4. **Better sub‑agent isolation** – `prepareSubagentSpawn` sets up isolated memory for any spawned agents, preventing cross‑talk while still giving them access to shared resources you define.\n\n5. **Observability & learning** – `afterTurn` lets you log, analyze, or even fine‑tune the agent’s behavior over time without manual review.\n\nIn practice, this means your agent stays true to its personality and instructions, can pull in your personal knowledge on demand, and handles long sessions or complex workflows without forgetting key constraints—making it far more reliable for automations, coding agents, or daily copilot use."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":38997,"output":324,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39321,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775205049964,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a30ff3c5ad041af8"}}
