{"type":"message","id":"850c2d7d","parentId":"9c5091dc","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:34:27.340Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-b169f538c9eb10af","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"r\": 11,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Any application that you're seeing will add a lot of, we are talking about real business value here. So enough of the application explanation. I talked about the system, right? Now it's time to build it for yourself, your own version of this. We will build that. Now we can go back here and this prompt gives you the scaffolding, the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point will connect real data integrate superbase and wire up agents in sections that follow so what we are essentially doing is we have\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 12,\n        \"cited_text\": \"minivax coding if you want to stay under 20 or something and you can even use google anti-gravity if you want to keep it you know completely free and use some gemini models to build the whole thing so the choice is up to you from this point you can use any tool to build what i am building and everything i'm building is the infrastructure where agents can live mission control a dashboard a kanban but whatever you want to call it this is just a beginning you are essentially creating a digital organization and digital office for your agents to come in and work that's where we deploy our\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 13,\n        \"cited_text\": \"🏁 Course Complete — Your Full Stack Twenty-Three Chapters. Here's What You Built. Dan Peguine: Full Agent List → chrysb: Founder Use Cases → Bhanu Teja: 10 Agents 24/7 → Calacanis: “Ultron” System → Clawdiverse: Community Collection → OpenClaw Radar: Guides & News → Playbooks: Full Skills Library → You didn't just learn a tool. You built an infrastructure. YOUR FULL STACK FOUNDATION Security (Ch 4) + Memory (Ch 8) + Token Optimization (Ch 3) BRAIN Business Brain L1–L3 (Ch 5–7) + ContextEngine INTERFACE Mission Control (Ch 9) + Task Board (Ch 11)\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"grand-forest","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"**Step 9** of the OpenClaw masterclass is titled **Mission Control Dashboard**, which focuses on building a real-time command center for your AI workforce [1, 2]. Known as **ClawBuddy Lite**, this dashboard provides a centralized interface to monitor agent profiles, live status, and operations [1, 3].\\n\\nThe key components and instructions for this step include:\\n\\n### **1. Building the UI Shell**\\n*   **Vibe Coding approach:** Unlike complex manual coding, this dashboard is built using a single, comprehensive prompt in \\\"vibe coding\\\" platforms like **Lovable**, Bolt, or Anti-gravity [3-5].\\n*   **The LiteKit Prompt:** This prompt generates a full UI scaffolding with five main tabs, a glass-morphic design, and animated transitions [3, 6].\\n*   **Included Features:** The initial shell provides placeholders for the **Command Deck, Agent Profiles, Kanban Board, AI Log, Agent Council,** and **Meeting Intelligence** [3, 5].\\n\\n### **2. Version Control and Deployment**\\n*   **GitHub Integration:** Once the shell is generated, you must connect it to **GitHub** using the `gh auth login` command in your terminal [7, 8].\\n*   **Tracking and Iteration:** Connecting GitHub allows your mission control to become a real, version-controlled product rather than just a prototype, enabling you to deploy it to platforms like **Netlify or Vercel** [8, 9].\\n\\n### **3. Monitoring Capabilities**\\n*   **Agent Visibility:** The dashboard features \\\"status rings\\\" and real-time visibility so you can see exactly which agents are online and what tasks they are currently performing [3, 10].\\n*   **Real-Time Data:** While Step 9 builds the \\\"shell,\\\" it serves as the foundation for subsequent steps where you integrate **Supabase** to connect real data and wire up your autonomous agents [3, 11].\\n\\nBy completing this step, you transition from managing agents via a command line or simple chat to having a professional-grade \\\"digital office\\\" for your organization [12, 13].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"2\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"3\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"4\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"5\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"6\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"7\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"9\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"10\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"11\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"12\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"13\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"This is what turns your agent from an assistant to autonomous operator. Chapter 8. Memory Architecture. Soul, identity, user context, agent, tools, daily memory logs. I'll walk you through every file, what goes where, how to prevent memory decay because OpenClaw will quietly drop your most important instructions if you don't set this up right. Chapter 9. Mission Control Dashboard We build a real command center from scratch, so you always know what your agents are doing. Full UI, agent profiles, live status monitoring.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 2,\n        \"cited_text\": \"which most people are conveniently ignoring and we will have agent foundations and dashboard in three and four what is foundation we will talk about memory self-evaluation and real-time machine control dashboard for your ai workforce and what does sections fight through seven cover we will talk about how to wire these tools together you know build a task board or map every feature that we have and every employee that we are going to build to a seven-stage business operations loop. That's what I was saying in previous section.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 3,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 9 Build Your Own Mission Control Your AI Command Center ClawBuddy Lite gives you a full dashboard with Kanban board, AI log, insights, status rings, and real-time agent visibility. Built with one Lovable prompt. [🐾 Masterclass Prompt ClawBuddy LiteKit Build a full AI agent command center dashboard with one Lovable prompt. Dark theme, glass-morphic, 5 tabs. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/clawbuddy-litekit) Note: This prompt gives you the scaffolding — the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point. We'll connect real data, integrate Supabase, and wire up agents in the sections that follow.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 4,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So why am I showing you this? So this is what we call, and you might have seen a bunch of people have these Kanban boards that ai is working and you and ai both working on things you giving and both ai building or some of the things that are completely and being taken care of ai itself so to build a board like this or to you can ask your agent to build this for you and they will but they won't be at this level they won't be this good looking if you will so i found out a hack is using if you go back to the master class it says flobbery live kit light kit so light\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 5,\n        \"cited_text\": \"the command deck we have agent profiles we have kanban board we have ai log agent council meeting intelligence premium design so we are copying this prompt and going to any you can go to a lovable or bolt or anything that you any vibe coding platform that you can think of and usually they will give you free credits right five credits or so they will give you and if you are you know if you someone refers you you get 10 more bonus credits so 15 credits i should we should be able to we can probably make this work.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 6,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Five credits i'll show you so i will paste the prompt and if you want to change the name here you can i don't want to add the word light kit and instead of claw buddy you can do it in any right now it is emerald green the old one was red so i don't mind uh it's being green right so I will just hit send. Right now it says thinking. And this is what you should be seeing. Not blank screen waiting for other instructions. So I'll build Cloverdy, a future CK, a common zone, glass morphic cards, Emerald Wax, and some animated transitions.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 7,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Perfect. Getting ready. This is awesome. So next up we have, We don't have to wait for it. If you go back, while the scaffolding is getting ready, we can work on our integration guide. So we are building this shell, right? So what happens once you build it? You have to find a way to bring that shell into your open floor, to give access to your open floor. How do you do that you do that by authenticating by connecting github so you can copy this command and you can go to your terminal and in the terminal you will once you run this,\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 8,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 10 Integrations & Skills Ecosystem Wire Everything Together Connect GitHub to Lovable + OpenClaw. Version control your dashboard from day one. Then unlock superpowers: browser control and email via AgentMail. Connect GitHub To connect GitHub to your OpenClaw account, run this in the terminal: Authenticate with GitHub CLI gh auth login Then connect your Lovable project to a GitHub repo so every change is tracked and deployable. Why this matters: Once GitHub is connected, you can push your ClawBuddy dashboard to a repo, deploy it to Netlify or Vercel, and iterate on it with AI agents. Your mission control becomes a real, version-controlled product — not just a prototype.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 9,\n        \"cited_text\": \"somewhere to the side so 7.37 so 2 minutes ago discovery call follow up and all of that it actually did all the tasks even from the previous task it created html files maybe they'll work in this machine but if you want to work and if you want to check these files even when you are using a phone somewhere away from the computer I would suggest you connect this to Netlify and you just ask it to deploy to Netlify and give me a link and it will do that so it was a simple fix plot code was able to change it so i can see\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 10,\n        \"cited_text\": \"And you didn't just learn it too, you built an infrastructure. So for the foundation, you have security, memory, and tokens. And for the brain, you have business brain that is level 1, 2, 3 based on where you are. and you now know about context engine no more. Open class, skipping, important stuff. So interface, you built a mission control and a task board. You exactly know how to. You know, you can see your agents working, you can assign your agents work, other agents can assign work and you can create custom cron jobs that super\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 11,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Any application that you're seeing will add a lot of, we are talking about real business value here. So enough of the application explanation. I talked about the system, right? Now it's time to build it for yourself, your own version of this. We will build that. Now we can go back here and this prompt gives you the scaffolding, the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point will connect real data integrate superbase and wire up agents in sections that follow so what we are essentially doing is we have\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 12,\n        \"cited_text\": \"minivax coding if you want to stay under 20 or something and you can even use google anti-gravity if you want to keep it you know completely free and use some gemini models to build the whole thing so the choice is up to you from this point you can use any tool to build what i am building and everything i'm building is the infrastructure where agents can live mission control a dashboard a kanban but whatever you want to call it this is just a beginning you are essentially creating a digital organization and digital office for your agents to come in and work that's where we deploy our\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 13,\n        \"cited_text\": \"🏁 Course Complete — Your Full Stack Twenty-Three Chapters. Here's What You Built. Dan Peguine: Full Agent List → chrysb: Founder Use Cases → Bhanu Teja: 10 Agents 24/7 → Calacanis: “Ultron” System → Clawdiverse: Community Collection → OpenClaw Radar: Guides & News → Playbooks: Full Skills Library → You didn't just learn a tool. You built an infrastructure. YOUR FULL STACK FOUNDATION Security (Ch 4) + Memory (Ch 8) + Token Optimization (Ch 3) BRAIN Business Brain L1–L3 (Ch 5–7) + ContextEngine INTERFACE Mission Control (Ch 9) + Task Board (Ch 11)\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","name":"nlm notebook"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775205267337}}
