{"type":"message","id":"550feaef","parentId":"29bd4e9f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:23:27.792Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-8b9b847c636f406b","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"n this in the terminal: Authenticate with GitHub CLI gh auth login Then connect your Lovable project to a GitHub repo so every change is tracked and deployable. Why this matters: Once GitHub is connected, you can push your ClawBuddy dashboard to a repo, deploy it to Netlify or Vercel, and iterate on it with AI agents. Your mission control becomes a real, version-controlled product — not just a prototype.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 13,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So the star of the show is still OpenClaw. this is an open floor masterclass the builders are helpers and you use them to construct the platform once then open floor runs the show forever and that's the system and that's why it works so why this matters because most people try to do everything in one tool and burn out they ask open floor to build orchestrate and execute and wonder why the results are mediocre And this masterclass separates the responsibilities cleanly. I can show you a finished application and say, hey, OpenClaw is doing all these amazing things.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 14,\n        \"cited_text\": \"The star of the show is still OpenClaw. The builders are helpers. You use them to construct the platform once. Then OpenClaw runs the show forever. That's the system. That's why it works. Why this matters: Most people try to do everything in one tool and burn out. They ask OpenClaw to build, orchestrate, AND execute — and wonder why the results are mediocre. This masterclass separates the responsibilities cleanly: ✓ Build once with the right tool (Claude Code, Lovable, Codex) — the platform, the dashboard, the databases ✓ Orchestrate forever with OpenClaw — dispatching tasks, running workflows, coordinating agents ✓ Execute on demand with specialized agents — each one trained for a specific job, reporting to the orchestrator\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"marine-falcon","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"The **dashboard UI shell scaffolding** for OpenClaw is built using a single, comprehensive prompt referred to as the **ClawBuddy LiteKit** [1]. This prompt is designed for \\\"vibe coding\\\" platforms like **Lovable**, **Bolt**, or **Anti-gravity** to generate a professional \\\"digital office\\\" for your AI workforce [1, 2].\\n\\n### **Core Components of the Scaffolding**\\nThe UI shell provides the full scaffolding, navigation, and pages with placeholder data, which are later wired to real data in Supabase [1, 3]. The primary tabs include:\\n*   **Command Deck:** The central interface for overseeing operations [1].\\n*   **Agent Profiles:** Dedicated cards for each agent (e.g., Ray, Pujihi) that display their **Soul, Identity, and Memory** files [1, 4].\\n*   **Kanban Board:** A 5-column task management system (To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, Done) [1, 5].\\n*   **AI Log:** A real-time record of agent activity, heartbeats, and task progress [1, 4].\\n*   **Agent Council:** A module where agents can \\\"debate\\\" and decide on tasks among themselves [1, 6].\\n*   **Meeting Intelligence:** An interface for **Jane** (the meeting assistant) to display transcripts, action items, and follow-up briefs [7, 8].\\n\\n### **Design Requirements**\\nTo achieve the \\\"million-dollar\\\" look described in the masterclass, the prompt should specify:\\n*   **Aesthetic:** Dark theme with a **glass-morphic design** [1, 9].\\n*   **Primary Accents:** Emerald green or futuristic color schemes [9, 10].\\n*   **Animations:** Smooth, animated transitions, hover effects, and glowing elements throughout the application [9, 11].\\n*   **Navigation:** A sidebar menu and an upgraded header [11].\\n*   **Visibility:** Real-time \\\"status rings\\\" to monitor agent visibility and online presence [1].\\n\\n### **Usage Context**\\nIn **Chapter 9**, you paste this prompt into a builder like Lovable to generate the UI [1]. Once the shell is ready, you connect it to **GitHub** (using `gh auth login`) to turn it into a version-controlled product that can be deployed to platforms like Netlify or Vercel [12]. This separation of roles allows the **Builder** to construct the UI while **OpenClaw** acts as the **Orchestrator** to manage the work forever [13, 14].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"2\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"3\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"4\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"5\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"6\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"7\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"9\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"10\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"11\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"12\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"13\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"14\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 9 Build Your Own Mission Control Your AI Command Center ClawBuddy Lite gives you a full dashboard with Kanban board, AI log, insights, status rings, and real-time agent visibility. Built with one Lovable prompt. [🐾 Masterclass Prompt ClawBuddy LiteKit Build a full AI agent command center dashboard with one Lovable prompt. Dark theme, glass-morphic, 5 tabs. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/clawbuddy-litekit) Note: This prompt gives you the scaffolding — the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point. We'll connect real data, integrate Supabase, and wire up agents in the sections that follow.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 2,\n        \"cited_text\": \"which most people are conveniently ignoring and we will have agent foundations and dashboard in three and four what is foundation we will talk about memory self-evaluation and real-time machine control dashboard for your ai workforce and what does sections fight through seven cover we will talk about how to wire these tools together you know build a task board or map every feature that we have and every employee that we are going to build to a seven-stage business operations loop. That's what I was saying in previous section.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 3,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Any application that you're seeing will add a lot of, we are talking about real business value here. So enough of the application explanation. I talked about the system, right? Now it's time to build it for yourself, your own version of this. We will build that. Now we can go back here and this prompt gives you the scaffolding, the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point will connect real data integrate superbase and wire up agents in sections that follow so what we are essentially doing is we have\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 4,\n        \"cited_text\": \"community and fork it with one button we have this is my place my agents live asian teams live we have skills factory and we have ability for ai asking questions ai log what they're doing the heartbeat and everything identity their soul files their memory files everything daily memory log being saved to memory. You know, where you can open and see what they worked on every single day for me. So multiple agents, this can be OpenClaw agent, this can be CloudCode agent, or any agent that can use API, they can be here.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 5,\n        \"cited_text\": \"🔌 Browse all skills at playbooks.com → 🌐 Community use cases at clawdiverse.com → Chapter 11 Task Management Agent-Powered Kanban 5 columns, drag-to-reorder, assignees, subtasks — the backbone of every autonomous workflow. Your agents create, move, and complete tasks on their own. [📋 Masterclass Prompt Kanban Board Task management with 5 columns (To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, Done), assignees, deadlines, subtasks, and drag-to-reorder. Full prompt to build it. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/kanban-board)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 6,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Discord as your AI team's Slack handle I'll show you how to set it up A server, I will meet my agent, set it up And these agents talk to each other They send alerts, request send updates and escalate when they need you. Every agent has its own bot, its own channel, its own presence. In chapter 20, I discuss how these agents can talk to each other. Agent communication. Instead of you going back and forth, agents asking is this okay, you let them sit in a council and discuss it among themselves. They debate, they decide, they come to you only when they need approval.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 7,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So in total, the AI system generated at least $54,000 in revenue for Brian within four days. Can you imagine AI generating 54,000 new revenue in four days? It blows my mind. And if you look at this system, one of the op-center applications is meeting intelligence. Brian's meeting, it analyzed around 30 meetings. But if you look at me, I have 1,614 meetings that AI can analyze and build things around. I can say, pick all the discovery calls and based on all the discovery calls, see if I missed any follow-ups or any action items.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 8,\n        \"cited_text\": \"One employee handles meetings. Another runs outreach. Another watches your competitors. None of them take days off. [🎙 Meeting Intelligence Fathom sync, auto-summaries, action items, prep briefs Prompt Ready](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/meeting-intelligence) [📞 Lexa — Phone Voice AI for inbound & outbound calls, appointments, follow-ups Prompt Ready](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/lexa) [📧 Nova — Email AI email agent with campaigns, templates, analytics, auto-replies Prompt Ready](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/email-assistant) [🎥\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 9,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Five credits i'll show you so i will paste the prompt and if you want to change the name here you can i don't want to add the word light kit and instead of claw buddy you can do it in any right now it is emerald green the old one was red so i don't mind uh it's being green right so I will just hit send. Right now it says thinking. And this is what you should be seeing. Not blank screen waiting for other instructions. So I'll build Cloverdy, a future CK, a common zone, glass morphic cards, Emerald Wax, and some animated transitions.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 10,\n        \"cited_text\": \"you already have a really good prompt but you don't have the plan that's what lovable is coming up with and if you look at this plan it shows a dark futuristic marketplace called claw alley and background our primary accent secondary accent yes claw alley list of services, contract review, and all of that amazing live feed, a header with bell size animation. Perfect. And I like what I see. Take a minute to read through the whole thing. At this point, if you see any discrepancies in what you want to see in the final\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 11,\n        \"cited_text\": \"CLI your open flow will have access to it I, can check do you have access to my guitar and to say yes they want me to clone anything copy anything usually if you don't want to now lovable finish generating it looks clean it looks we have the tabs we have a console we have meetings which is nice it has everything that i actually asked for what we are building. I want a visual overall, I want this application to be like a million dollars we should have a sidebar menu and, upgrade the header add some gloss morphic designs add some hover and glow animations\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 12,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 10 Integrations & Skills Ecosystem Wire Everything Together Connect GitHub to Lovable + OpenClaw. Version control your dashboard from day one. Then unlock superpowers: browser control and email via AgentMail. Connect GitHub To connect GitHub to your OpenClaw account, run this in the terminal: Authenticate with GitHub CLI gh auth login Then connect your Lovable project to a GitHub repo so every change is tracked and deployable. Why this matters: Once GitHub is connected, you can push your ClawBuddy dashboard to a repo, deploy it to Netlify or Vercel, and iterate on it with AI agents. Your mission control becomes a real, version-controlled product — not just a prototype.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 13,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So the star of the show is still OpenClaw. this is an open floor masterclass the builders are helpers and you use them to construct the platform once then open floor runs the show forever and that's the system and that's why it works so why this matters because most people try to do everything in one tool and burn out they ask open floor to build orchestrate and execute and wonder why the results are mediocre And this masterclass separates the responsibilities cleanly. I can show you a finished application and say, hey, OpenClaw is doing all these amazing things.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 14,\n        \"cited_text\": \"The star of the show is still OpenClaw. The builders are helpers. You use them to construct the platform once. Then OpenClaw runs the show forever. That's the system. That's why it works. Why this matters: Most people try to do everything in one tool and burn out. They ask OpenClaw to build, orchestrate, AND execute — and wonder why the results are mediocre. This masterclass separates the responsibilities cleanly: ✓ Build once with the right tool (Claude Code, Lovable, Codex) — the platform, the dashboard, the databases ✓ Orchestrate forever with OpenClaw — dispatching tasks, running workflows, coordinating agents ✓ Execute on demand with specialized agents — each one trained for a specific job, reporting to the orchestrator\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","name":"nlm notebook"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775215407786}}
