{"type":"message","id":"35472f11","parentId":"3272fc94","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:24:06.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We need to wait a bit more"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a99a0e33af21e98e","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"nimble-fjord","timeout":15000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":38060,"output":34,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38094,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775215441040,"responseId":"chatcmpl-bf8e3857b01adb4e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"46b8a357","parentId":"35472f11","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:24:12.176Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a99a0e33af21e98e","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"The **ClawBuddy Mission Control Dashboard** (also referred to as **ClawBuddy Lite**) is a real-time command center for your AI workforce, built from scratch in **Chapter 9** of the OpenClaw masterclass [1, 2]. It is designed to transition you from managing agents via a command line to having a professional \\\"digital office\\\" where you can monitor agent profiles, live status, and autonomous operations [2, 3].\\n\\n### **Building with Lovable (Vibe Coding)**\\nInstead of manual coding, the dashboard is constructed using a \\\"vibe coding\\\" approach on platforms like **Lovable**, Bolt, or Anti-gravity [2, 4]. \\n*   **The LiteKit Prompt:** You use a single, comprehensive copy-paste prompt (the **ClawBuddy LiteKit**) to generate the full UI scaffolding [5, 6]. \\n*   **Output:** This generates a dark-themed, glass-morphic UI shell with smooth animated transitions and five main navigation tabs [2, 4, 7].\\n\\n### **Core Dashboard Components**\\nThe UI generated by Lovable includes placeholders and navigation for:\\n*   **Command Deck:** The central oversight interface [2, 4].\\n*   **Agent Profiles:** Dedicated cards for each agent (e.g., Ray or Pujihi) showing their **Soul, Identity, and Memory** files [1, 2, 4].\\n*   **Kanban Board:** A five-column task management system (To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, Done) where agents autonomously move tasks [4, 8].\\n*   **AI Log:** A real-time record of all agent activities and heartbeat checks [2, 4].\\n*   **Specialized Modules:** Active tabs for the **Agent Council** (for agent-to-agent debate) and **Meeting Intelligence** (Jane) [4, 9].\\n\\n### **The Workflow: From Shell to Product**\\nThe process follows a specific sequence to turn the Lovable prototype into a functional business tool:\\n1.  **Generate the Shell:** Paste the LiteKit prompt into Lovable to create the UI and navigation [2, 4].\\n2.  **GitHub Connection:** Authenticate your terminal using `gh auth login` and connect your Lovable project to a **GitHub repository** [10, 11]. This turns your mission control into a version-controlled product that can be deployed to **Netlify** or **Vercel** [11].\\n3.  **Wire Real Data:** Once the visual shell is ready, you move to subsequent chapters to integrate **Supabase** to connect real data and wire up your autonomous agents [6, 12].\\n\\nThis separation of roles allows **Lovable** to act as the **Builder** (constructing the platform once), while **OpenClaw** acts as the **Orchestrator** to manage the work forever [13, 14].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"2\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"3\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"4\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"5\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"6\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"7\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"9\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"10\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"11\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"12\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"13\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"14\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"This is what turns your agent from an assistant to autonomous operator. Chapter 8. Memory Architecture. Soul, identity, user context, agent, tools, daily memory logs. I'll walk you through every file, what goes where, how to prevent memory decay because OpenClaw will quietly drop your most important instructions if you don't set this up right. Chapter 9. Mission Control Dashboard We build a real command center from scratch, so you always know what your agents are doing. Full UI, agent profiles, live status monitoring.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 2,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 9 Build Your Own Mission Control Your AI Command Center ClawBuddy Lite gives you a full dashboard with Kanban board, AI log, insights, status rings, and real-time agent visibility. Built with one Lovable prompt. [🐾 Masterclass Prompt ClawBuddy LiteKit Build a full AI agent command center dashboard with one Lovable prompt. Dark theme, glass-morphic, 5 tabs. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/clawbuddy-litekit) Note: This prompt gives you the scaffolding — the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point. We'll connect real data, integrate Supabase, and wire up agents in the sections that follow.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 3,\n        \"cited_text\": \"CHAPTERS 9–11 Dashboard, Integrations & Kanban Mission control dashboard, GitHub + browser + email wiring, skills ecosystem, and a full task management board. CHAPTERS 12–13 Builder/Orchestrator/Executor & Ops Loop The framework that changed everything. Three roles, seven business stages, zero gaps. CHAPTERS 14–17 AI Employees Meeting intelligence, AI SDR & email engine, voice AI phone agent, and a Typeform clone with webhooks. CHAPTERS 18–22 Multi-Agent, Council & Automations Agent-to-agent orchestration, Discord comms, Agent Council debates, the 8-phase pipeline, and scheduled cron jobs.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 4,\n        \"cited_text\": \"the command deck we have agent profiles we have kanban board we have ai log agent council meeting intelligence premium design so we are copying this prompt and going to any you can go to a lovable or bolt or anything that you any vibe coding platform that you can think of and usually they will give you free credits right five credits or so they will give you and if you are you know if you someone refers you you get 10 more bonus credits so 15 credits i should we should be able to we can probably make this work.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 5,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So why am I showing you this? So this is what we call, and you might have seen a bunch of people have these Kanban boards that ai is working and you and ai both working on things you giving and both ai building or some of the things that are completely and being taken care of ai itself so to build a board like this or to you can ask your agent to build this for you and they will but they won't be at this level they won't be this good looking if you will so i found out a hack is using if you go back to the master class it says flobbery live kit light kit so light\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 6,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Any application that you're seeing will add a lot of, we are talking about real business value here. So enough of the application explanation. I talked about the system, right? Now it's time to build it for yourself, your own version of this. We will build that. Now we can go back here and this prompt gives you the scaffolding, the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point will connect real data integrate superbase and wire up agents in sections that follow so what we are essentially doing is we have\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 7,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Five credits i'll show you so i will paste the prompt and if you want to change the name here you can i don't want to add the word light kit and instead of claw buddy you can do it in any right now it is emerald green the old one was red so i don't mind uh it's being green right so I will just hit send. Right now it says thinking. And this is what you should be seeing. Not blank screen waiting for other instructions. So I'll build Cloverdy, a future CK, a common zone, glass morphic cards, Emerald Wax, and some animated transitions.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 8,\n        \"cited_text\": \"You will need more openclaw agents work for you and this is the best way, you know, what's the best way to start building your dashboard from day one keeping in mind you are adding more more regions down the line so that is the key so if you look at what this has the board it has five columns and one workflow you can add more by the way five made sense for me to do doing needs input done and cancelled every task starts in to do moves to doing and wait and when an agent or human picks it up so goes to needs input if blocked and if ai agent\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 9,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Discord as your AI team's Slack handle I'll show you how to set it up A server, I will meet my agent, set it up And these agents talk to each other They send alerts, request send updates and escalate when they need you. Every agent has its own bot, its own channel, its own presence. In chapter 20, I discuss how these agents can talk to each other. Agent communication. Instead of you going back and forth, agents asking is this okay, you let them sit in a council and discuss it among themselves. They debate, they decide, they come to you only when they need approval.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 10,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Perfect. Getting ready. This is awesome. So next up we have, We don't have to wait for it. If you go back, while the scaffolding is getting ready, we can work on our integration guide. So we are building this shell, right? So what happens once you build it? You have to find a way to bring that shell into your open floor, to give access to your open floor. How do you do that you do that by authenticating by connecting github so you can copy this command and you can go to your terminal and in the terminal you will once you run this,\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 11,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 10 Integrations & Skills Ecosystem Wire Everything Together Connect GitHub to Lovable + OpenClaw. Version control your dashboard from day one. Then unlock superpowers: browser control and email via AgentMail. Connect GitHub To connect GitHub to your OpenClaw account, run this in the terminal: Authenticate with GitHub CLI gh auth login Then connect your Lovable project to a GitHub repo so every change is tracked and deployable. Why this matters: Once GitHub is connected, you can push your ClawBuddy dashboard to a repo, deploy it to Netlify or Vercel, and iterate on it with AI agents. Your mission control becomes a real, version-controlled product — not just a prototype.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 12,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Started because we had to build our handband board right so without further ado. Let's continue we have the repo we will copy that repo and the next step is actually setting up the, the next step is actually setting up our super base and let's clone the repo and. Okay it's just the UI and scaffolding we are building every feature step by step starting with the super base integration so, take a look and tell me what needs fixing so it's a solid scaffold nothing broken but it's not ready for real data yet\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 13,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So the star of the show is still OpenClaw. this is an open floor masterclass the builders are helpers and you use them to construct the platform once then open floor runs the show forever and that's the system and that's why it works so why this matters because most people try to do everything in one tool and burn out they ask open floor to build orchestrate and execute and wonder why the results are mediocre And this masterclass separates the responsibilities cleanly. I can show you a finished application and say, hey, OpenClaw is doing all these amazing things.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 14,\n        \"cited_text\": \"The star of the show is still OpenClaw. The builders are helpers. You use them to construct the platform once. Then OpenClaw runs the show forever. That's the system. That's why it works. Why this matters: Most people try to do everything in one tool and burn out. They ask OpenClaw to build, orchestrate, AND execute — and wonder why the results are mediocre. This masterclass separates the responsibilities cleanly: ✓ Build once with the right tool (Claude Code, Lovable, Codex) — the platform, the dashboard, the databases ✓ Orchestrate forever with OpenClaw — dispatching tasks, running workflows, coordinating agents ✓ Execute on demand with specialized agents — each one trained for a specific job, reporting to the orchestrator\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"nimble-fjord","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"The **ClawBuddy Mission Control Dashboard** (also referred to as **ClawBuddy Lite**) is a real-time command center for your AI workforce, built from scratch in **Chapter 9** of the OpenClaw masterclass [1, 2]. It is designed to transition you from managing agents via a command line to having a professional \\\"digital office\\\" where you can monitor agent profiles, live status, and autonomous operations [2, 3].\\n\\n### **Building with Lovable (Vibe Coding)**\\nInstead of manual coding, the dashboard is constructed using a \\\"vibe coding\\\" approach on platforms like **Lovable**, Bolt, or Anti-gravity [2, 4]. \\n*   **The LiteKit Prompt:** You use a single, comprehensive copy-paste prompt (the **ClawBuddy LiteKit**) to generate the full UI scaffolding [5, 6]. \\n*   **Output:** This generates a dark-themed, glass-morphic UI shell with smooth animated transitions and five main navigation tabs [2, 4, 7].\\n\\n### **Core Dashboard Components**\\nThe UI generated by Lovable includes placeholders and navigation for:\\n*   **Command Deck:** The central oversight interface [2, 4].\\n*   **Agent Profiles:** Dedicated cards for each agent (e.g., Ray or Pujihi) showing their **Soul, Identity, and Memory** files [1, 2, 4].\\n*   **Kanban Board:** A five-column task management system (To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, Done) where agents autonomously move tasks [4, 8].\\n*   **AI Log:** A real-time record of all agent activities and heartbeat checks [2, 4].\\n*   **Specialized Modules:** Active tabs for the **Agent Council** (for agent-to-agent debate) and **Meeting Intelligence** (Jane) [4, 9].\\n\\n### **The Workflow: From Shell to Product**\\nThe process follows a specific sequence to turn the Lovable prototype into a functional business tool:\\n1.  **Generate the Shell:** Paste the LiteKit prompt into Lovable to create the UI and navigation [2, 4].\\n2.  **GitHub Connection:** Authenticate your terminal using `gh auth login` and connect your Lovable project to a **GitHub repository** [10, 11]. This turns your mission control into a version-controlled product that can be deployed to **Netlify** or **Vercel** [11].\\n3.  **Wire Real Data:** Once the visual shell is ready, you move to subsequent chapters to integrate **Supabase** to connect real data and wire up your autonomous agents [6, 12].\\n\\nThis separation of roles allows **Lovable** to act as the **Builder** (constructing the platform once), while **OpenClaw** acts as the **Orchestrator** to manage the work forever [13, 14].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"2\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"3\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"4\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"5\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"6\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"7\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"9\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"10\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"11\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"12\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"13\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"14\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"This is what turns your agent from an assistant to autonomous operator. Chapter 8. Memory Architecture. Soul, identity, user context, agent, tools, daily memory logs. I'll walk you through every file, what goes where, how to prevent memory decay because OpenClaw will quietly drop your most important instructions if you don't set this up right. Chapter 9. Mission Control Dashboard We build a real command center from scratch, so you always know what your agents are doing. Full UI, agent profiles, live status monitoring.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 2,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 9 Build Your Own Mission Control Your AI Command Center ClawBuddy Lite gives you a full dashboard with Kanban board, AI log, insights, status rings, and real-time agent visibility. Built with one Lovable prompt. [🐾 Masterclass Prompt ClawBuddy LiteKit Build a full AI agent command center dashboard with one Lovable prompt. Dark theme, glass-morphic, 5 tabs. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/clawbuddy-litekit) Note: This prompt gives you the scaffolding — the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point. We'll connect real data, integrate Supabase, and wire up agents in the sections that follow.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 3,\n        \"cited_text\": \"CHAPTERS 9–11 Dashboard, Integrations & Kanban Mission control dashboard, GitHub + browser + email wiring, skills ecosystem, and a full task management board. CHAPTERS 12–13 Builder/Orchestrator/Executor & Ops Loop The framework that changed everything. Three roles, seven business stages, zero gaps. CHAPTERS 14–17 AI Employees Meeting intelligence, AI SDR & email engine, voice AI phone agent, and a Typeform clone with webhooks. CHAPTERS 18–22 Multi-Agent, Council & Automations Agent-to-agent orchestration, Discord comms, Agent Council debates, the 8-phase pipeline, and scheduled cron jobs.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n   