{"type":"message","id":"88218d2f","parentId":"2f220f4a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:25:30.061Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We need to proceed with Step 9: Mission Control Dashboard. The browser is unavailable, so we'll need to guide you through building the dashboard. Based on the notebook, Step 9 requires using **Lovable** (a vibe coding platform) with the **ClawBuddy LiteKit** prompt to generate the UI shell. Since I can't access Lovable directly, here's how we'll execute:\n\n## 🚀 Step 9 Execution Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Generate Dashboard UI Shell\n\n**Option A: Use Lovable (Recommended)**\n1. Go to [lovable.dev](https://lovable.dev) (sign up if needed — they give free credits)\n2. Create a new project\n3. Paste the **ClawBuddy LiteKit prompt** (I'll provide it below)\n4. Let Lovable generate the dark-themed, glass-morphic dashboard with 5 tabs\n\n**ClawBuddy LiteKit Prompt:**\n```\nBuild a full AI agent command center dashboard called \"ClawBuddy\". Dark theme with glass-morphic cards, emerald green accents, smooth animated transitions.\n\nInclude 5 main navigation tabs:\n1. **Command Deck** - Central oversight interface with status rings and live agent visibility\n2. **Agent Profiles** - Cards for each agent showing their Soul, Identity, and Memory files\n3. **Kanban Board** - 5 columns: To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, Done - where agents move tasks autonomously\n4. **AI Log** - Real-time record of all agent activities and heartbeat checks\n5. **Agent Council** - Tab for agent-to-agent debate and meeting intelligence\n\nEach tab should have:\n- Dark glass-morphic card design\n- Status indicators (green/yellow/red)\n- Smooth hover and transition animations\n- Responsive layout for desktop\n\nThe dashboard should feel like a professional mission control for managing AI agents.\n```\n\n### Phase 2: Connect GitHub (Version Control)\n\nAfter Lovable generates the UI:\n```bash\n# Authenticate GitHub CLI\ngh auth login\n\n# Create a new repo and push\ngh repo create clawbuddy-dashboard --public --source=. --push\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Deploy to Netlify/Vercel\n\n```bash\n# Install Netlify CLI (if using Netlify)\nnpm install -g netlify-cli\n\n# Deploy\nnetlify deploy --prod\n```\n\n### Phase 4: Wire Real Data (Supabase)\n\nLater chapters will integrate Supabase for real-time data. For now, the scaffold provides placeholder data.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ What I Need From You\n\n1. **Do you want to use Lovable?** If yes, go to lovable.dev, paste the prompt, and share the generated repo URL. I can then help wire it to OpenClaw.\n\n2. **Alternative:** If you prefer building locally, I can create a basic React/Vite dashboard in your workspace that connects to OpenClaw's CLI commands.\n\nWhich approach do you want? I'll proceed based on your choice."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":42191,"output":631,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775215491801,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8bf813a04a02f956"}}
