{"type":"message","id":"255f1149","parentId":"76b96854","timestamp":"2026-04-04T23:46:27.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Top Activities in Postojna — Monday (tomorrow):**\n\n1. **🦇 Postojna Cave** — Most visited cave in Europe! 40+ million visitors. Underground train ride through stunning stalactites. Book ahead.\n\n2. **🏰 Predjama Castle** — Medieval castle built into a cliff face. 9km from Postojna. Dramatic setting, fascinating history.\n\n3. **🚴 Cycling & Hiking** — With 17°C and zero rain, perfect for exploring karst landscapes. Bike rentals available in town.\n\n4. **🦎 Cave Proteus (Olm)** — See the \"human fish\" — endemic blind salamander found only in these caves.\n\n5. **🍷 Wine Tasting** — Local karst region wines (Teran, Refošk). Nearby vineyards offer tastings.\n\n6. **📸 Nature Photography** — Clear skies = great shots of cave entrances, castle, and rolling hills.\n\n7. **🍽️ Local Cuisine** — Try jota (bean stew), pršut (prosciutto), and local cheeses at traditional gostilnas.\n\n**Weather for tomorrow:** Sunny, ~17°C, zero rain. Perfect day for outdoor exploring!\n\n**Pro tip:** Combine Postojna Cave + Predjama Castle in one trip — they're close and often sold as a combo ticket.\n\nWant me to check opening hours or book anything?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":67452,"output":294,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67746,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775346355818,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8a79d3577fa4cd7c"}}
