{"type":"message","id":"2f858f29","parentId":"73549095","timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:02:06.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right — this is a problem. The dashboard shows \"starting\" because the task system doesn't have a proper scheduling/notification mechanism built in. I have no way to automatically trigger at 8:00 — I only react to heartbeats or messages. **Here's how we fix it:** 1. **Cron job** — Set up a system cron that pings me at 8:00 daily to check tasks and send reminders 2. **External scheduler** — Use a service like cron-job.org or a simple script that hits an endpoint 3. **OpenClaw cron** — If OpenClaw has a scheduler, we configure it to trigger reminder checks Let me check if OpenClaw has built-in scheduling:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b2df86e5a594337a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron --help"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":82078,"output":166,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775541694493,"responseId":"chatcmpl-99352234aa9f34b1"}}
