{"type":"message","id":"e572e9ff","parentId":"44a8b621","timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:15:09.001Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-b1160a5b0b719be4","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session tidy-reef, pid 7100). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"tidy-reef","pid":7100,"startedAt":1775542498984,"cwd":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace","tail":""},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775542508995}}
{"type":"message","id":"65544ce2","parentId":"e572e9ff","timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:15:22.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a082618e987bea99","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"tidy-reef","timeout":15000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":91562,"output":27,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91589,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775542509016,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a70cfdbf4f7cb19c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cb77f9a","parentId":"65544ce2","timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:15:22.200Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a082618e987bea99","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"8-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 17,\n        \"cited_text\": \"table rights including action update for column moves and proper to do if you want i'll do the implementation pass now current tasks data with this api and, create update design we want to make this accessible for other agents to come in and work on our clobody application as well. So, let's set it up. And mind you, you are setting the whole thing up. This doesn't exist. Are we on the same page so codex is taking a long time to get back and i feel like you know plot code is sometimes even better and actually showing what is going on 100\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 18,\n        \"cited_text\": \"doesn't have a key an api key that will do the job or certain permission a capture that only human can solve that's where it goes to needs input and the task is blocked and done which are completed and cancelled and also this is a good metric to have in your main dashboard as well because. You can see how many tasks that were completed that day or previous day. So if you look at AI tasks that are completed this week, and it's only Thursday, we already have all of this, right? And, you know, Sherlock, Discord bot online, CloudBrain, and I have multiple agents here.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 19,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Okay, where do we go from here? Now that we have three roles, the builder, orchestrator, and executor, we will be building applications that are absolutely important to make this work. So for example, we are building Kanban board because you know where your agents are working, what they're working on, and they have a place for you to give inputs, additional inputs. When they are stuck they can move the task to needs input and you can come in give additional context so they can keep working and it works with open claw\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tidy-reef","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"Chapters 9 through 11 focus on transitioning your AI from a standard chatbot into a professional **\\\"digital office\\\"** by building a command center, wiring it to the real world, and establishing a backbone for autonomous task management [1, 2].\\n\\n### **Chapter 9: Mission Control Dashboard (ClawBuddy Lite)**\\nThis chapter builds a real-time command center from scratch to monitor agent activity and health [1].\\n*   **The Build:** It uses the **ClawBuddy LiteKit prompt** in a vibe-coding platform like Lovable or Bolt to generate a **dark-themed, glass-morphic UI** with emerald green accents [3, 4].\\n*   **Core Structure:** The dashboard includes five primary navigation tabs: **Command Deck** (oversight), **Agent Profiles** (identity files), **Kanban Board** (task tracking), **AI Log** (activity history), and **Specialized Modules** for councils and meetings [4-6].\\n*   **Real-Time Monitoring:** The interface features **status rings** and visibility into agent heartbeats, ensuring you know exactly which agents are online and what they are working on [4].\\n\\n### **Chapter 10: Integrations & Skills Ecosystem**\\nThis section wires agents to external tools so they can interact with the real world rather than just processing text [2].\\n*   **GitHub Integration:** By running `gh auth login` in the terminal, you connect your dashboard to a repository, turning it into a **version-controlled product** that can be deployed to Netlify or Vercel [7].\\n*   **Browser Control:** Using the **OpenClaw Browser Relay** and a Chrome Extension (configured to **Port 18792**), agents gain \\\"eyes on the web,\\\" allowing them to navigate pages, click buttons, and scrape data via natural language [8, 9].\\n*   **Email via AgentMail:** This provides agents with a **programmatic inbox** (e.g., `raybot@agentmail.to`) to send outreach and receive replies without the complexity of the Gmail API or OAuth [10].\\n*   **Skills Ecosystem:** Instead of building every feature by hand, you can install pre-packaged community \\\"plugins\\\" (e.g., `meeting-to-action`) with a single command: `$ npx playbooks add skill...` [11, 12].\\n\\n### **Chapter 11: Task Management (Agent-Powered Kanban)**\\nThe Kanban board serves as the **backbone of the autonomous workflow**, where agents pick up, execute, and report on work independently [2, 13].\\n*   **The 5-Column System:** Tasks move through a structured pipeline: **To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, and Done** [13, 14].\\n*   **Autonomous Handoff:** Every task begins in \\\"To Do.\\\" When an agent picks it up, it moves to \\\"Doing\\\" and initiates the **8-phase pipeline** (Context, Plan, Build, Validate, Heal, Retest, Report, and Close) [14, 15].\\n*   **The API Contract:** To support multi-agent orchestration, the system transitions from direct database access to an **API-first contract** (`ai-tasks` endpoint). This ensures different agents (e.g., \\\"Ray\\\" or \\\"Pujihi\\\") can collaborate on the same board without breaking data structures [16, 17].\\n*   **Human-in-the-Loop:** If an agent is blocked by a missing API key or a captcha, it autonomously moves the task to **\\\"Needs Input,\\\"** alerting the human operator to provide the necessary context [18, 19].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"2\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"3\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"4\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"5\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"6\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"7\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"8\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"9\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"10\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"11\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"12\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"13\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n      \"14\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"15\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"16\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"17\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"18\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"19\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"This is what turns your agent from an assistant to autonomous operator. Chapter 8. Memory Architecture. Soul, identity, user context, agent, tools, daily memory logs. I'll walk you through every file, what goes where, how to prevent memory decay because OpenClaw will quietly drop your most important instructions if you don't set this up right. Chapter 9. Mission Control Dashboard We build a real command center from scratch, so you always know what your agents are doing. Full UI, agent profiles, live status monitoring.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 2,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 10. Integrations GitHub, browser control, email via agent mail. Wiring everything together so your agents can actually interact with the real world. Chapter 11. Task Management A full Kanban board where your agents pick up tasks, move them through stages, and file reports. To do, doing, needs input, done. All autonomous. Chapter 12. Builder, Orchestrator, and Executor. This is the framework that changed everything for me. Your builder constructs platforms and your orchestrator, that's OpenTlock, manages workflows.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 3,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Five credits i'll show you so i will paste the prompt and if you want to change the name here you can i don't want to add the word light kit and instead of claw buddy you can do it in any right now it is emerald green the old one was red so i don't mind uh it's being green right so I will just hit send. Right now it says thinking. And this is what you should be seeing. Not blank screen waiting for other instructions. So I'll build Cloverdy, a future CK, a common zone, glass morphic cards, Emerald Wax, and some animated transitions.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 4,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 9 Build Your Own Mission Control Your AI Command Center ClawBuddy Lite gives you a full dashboard with Kanban board, AI log, insights, status rings, and real-time agent visibility. Built with one Lovable prompt. [🐾 Masterclass Prompt ClawBuddy LiteKit Build a full AI agent command center dashboard with one Lovable prompt. Dark theme, glass-morphic, 5 tabs. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/clawbuddy-litekit) Note: This prompt gives you the scaffolding — the full UI shell with all tabs, pages, and navigation. It's a starting point. We'll connect real data, integrate Supabase, and wire up agents in the sections that follow.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 5,\n        \"cited_text\": \"the command deck we have agent profiles we have kanban board we have ai log agent council meeting intelligence premium design so we are copying this prompt and going to any you can go to a lovable or bolt or anything that you any vibe coding platform that you can think of and usually they will give you free credits right five credits or so they will give you and if you are you know if you someone refers you you get 10 more bonus credits so 15 credits i should we should be able to we can probably make this work.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 6,\n        \"cited_text\": \"CLI your open flow will have access to it I, can check do you have access to my guitar and to say yes they want me to clone anything copy anything usually if you don't want to now lovable finish generating it looks clean it looks we have the tabs we have a console we have meetings which is nice it has everything that i actually asked for what we are building. I want a visual overall, I want this application to be like a million dollars we should have a sidebar menu and, upgrade the header add some gloss morphic designs add some hover and glow animations\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 7,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Chapter 10 Integrations & Skills Ecosystem Wire Everything Together Connect GitHub to Lovable + OpenClaw. Version control your dashboard from day one. Then unlock superpowers: browser control and email via AgentMail. Connect GitHub To connect GitHub to your OpenClaw account, run this in the terminal: Authenticate with GitHub CLI gh auth login Then connect your Lovable project to a GitHub repo so every change is tracked and deployable. Why this matters: Once GitHub is connected, you can push your ClawBuddy dashboard to a repo, deploy it to Netlify or Vercel, and iterate on it with AI agents. Your mission control becomes a real, version-controlled product — not just a prototype.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 8,\n        \"cited_text\": \"⚡ Give Superpowers to Your OpenClaw Out of the box, OpenClaw can read files, write code, and run commands. But it can't see your browser or send emails. These two integrations change that. 🌐 Browser Control OpenClaw Browser Relay + Chrome Extension Attach OpenClaw to a live Chrome tab. Navigate pages, click buttons, fill forms, scrape data — all from natural language. Your agent gets eyes on the web. // Setup SOP — paste this as your prompt Step 1: Set tokens (both must match) Step 2: Sync the service (fixes daemon drift)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 9,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Step 3: Validate relay health Step 4: Chrome Extension config Port: 18792 • Token: same as above • Save Common Pitfalls: Tokens must be identical — mismatch = unauthorized __OPENCLAW_REDACTED__ can get saved as a literal token if copied blindly Extension only works on https:// tabs — not chrome:// or extension pages If badge won't turn green: check site access in chrome://extensions → extension details After config changes, always run stop → install --force → start Verify it works: Attach tab (badge green) → ask OpenClaw to navigate to example.com → confirm it moves in your actual Chrome window\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 10,\n        \"cited_text\": \"✉ Email via AgentMail Give your agent its own email address AgentMail gives your AI agent a real email inbox. Send outreach, receive replies, parse responses — all programmatically. No Gmail API, no OAuth headaches. // Setup — paste this as your prompt Step 1: Get your API key Sign up at agentmail.to → grab your API key from the dashboard. Step 2: Install the SDK Step 3: Create an inbox Step 4: Send email API Gotchas: Send endpoint: /inboxes/{id}/messages/send — NOT /messages to field must be an array of strings, not a plain string Use client.inboxes.messages.send() — NOT client.messages.send() List inboxes: client.inboxes.list().inboxes — NOT .data\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 11,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Use cases: Lead outreach, meeting follow-ups, daily report delivery, client onboarding sequences, support ticket responses 🔌 What Are Skills? Everything you just did — connecting GitHub, setting up browser control, wiring up email — you built that by hand. And that's important because you need to understand how it works under the hood. But there's a faster way. OpenClaw has a skills ecosystem . Think of skills like plugins — community-built packages that give your agent a new ability in one command. There's a skill for email management, a skill for meeting notes, a skill for content creation, a skill for generating proposals. Hundreds of them. And they're all open source — you can read every line, modify anything, or use them as a starting point for your own.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 12,\n        \"cited_text\": \"To install a skill, it's one line: $ npx playbooks add skill openclaw/skills --skill meeting-to-action That just gave your agent the ability to turn any meeting transcript into action items with owners and deadlines. One command. Throughout the rest of this course, after certain chapters, you'll see what we call a “Pro Move.” It's a community skill or a real-world example of someone using exactly what was just taught — at scale. Extra credit. You don't need it, but if you want to go further, it's there.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"8954446d-b965-4214-9f10-f8a8c4fbb713\",\n        \"citation_number\": 13,\n        \"cited_text\": \"🔌 Browse all skills at playbooks.com → 🌐 Community use cases at clawdiverse.com → Chapter 11 Task Management Agent-Powered Kanban 5 columns, drag-to-reorder, assignees, subtasks — the backbone of every autonomous workflow. Your agents create, move, and complete tasks on their own. [📋 Masterclass Prompt Kanban Board Task management with 5 columns (To Do, Doing, Needs Input, Canceled, Done), assignees, deadlines, subtasks, and drag-to-reorder. Full prompt to build it. →](https://masterclass-prompts.netlify.app/kanban-board)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 14,\n        \"cited_text\": \"You will need more openclaw agents work for you and this is the best way, you know, what's the best way to start building your dashboard from day one keeping in mind you are adding more more regions down the line so that is the key so if you look at what this has the board it has five columns and one workflow you can add more by the way five made sense for me to do doing needs input done and cancelled every task starts in to do moves to doing and wait and when an agent or human picks it up so goes to needs input if blocked and if ai agent\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 15,\n        \"cited_text\": \"So a lot of you don't know what eight phase pipeline is. It is like an autopilot, autonomous sequence. I will show you what that means in future sections. But just know your agents can assign tasks to other regions that will do every build every task in in a eight phase sequence they you know then as soon as they receive a command they don't just jump in blind you have to set context plan and then you know create the task and once the task is created you build after building you test if it breaks you have to heal and then\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 16,\n        \"cited_text\": \"And I think you are a kind of person who want to make it so you can use it with other agents as well because multi-agent is the future. So keeping that in mind, let's go to our presentation and copy our prompt. This prompt is kanbanboardapireference.md. so I will give this to our open log and paste it here and human creates tasks for agent so it has a lot of super base related things and now you will see what perfect this is exactly what I needed i'll read this as a source of truth and switch our integration plan to the ai tasks endpoint contract not direct\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 17,\n        \"cited_text\": \"table rights including action update for column moves and proper to do if you want i'll do the implementation pass now current tasks data with this api and, create update design we want to make this accessible for other agents to come in and work on our clobody application as well. So, let's set it up. And mind you, you are setting the whole thing up. This doesn't exist. Are we on the same page so codex is taking a long time to get back and i feel like you know plot code is sometimes even better and actually showing what is going on 100\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 18,\n        \"cited_text\": \"doesn't have a key an api key that will do the job or certain permission a capture that only human can solve that's where it goes to needs input and the task is blocked and done which are completed and cancelled and also this is a good metric to have in your main dashboard as well because. You can see how many tasks that were completed that day or previous day. So if you look at AI tasks that are completed this week, and it's only Thursday, we already have all of this, right? And, you know, Sherlock, Discord bot online, CloudBrain, and I have multiple agents here.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 19,\n        \"cited_text\": \"Okay, where do we go from here? Now that we have three roles, the builder, orchestrator, and executor, we will be building applications that are absolutely important to make this work. So for example, we are building Kanban board because you know where your agents are working, what they're working on, and they have a place for you to give inputs, additional inputs. When they are stuck they can move the task to needs input and you can come in give additional context so they can keep working and it works with open claw\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","name":"nlm notebook"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775542522197}}
{"type":"message","id":"731c0e25","parentId":"6cb77f9a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:15:50.829Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my queries, here's what I found for **Step 10: Integrations & Skills Ecosystem**: ## 📋 Step 10 Execution Plan: Integrations & Skills Ecosystem ### 🎯 Goal Wire everything together — GitHub, browser control, and email via AgentMail — then unlock the skills ecosystem. ### 📖 What the Notebook Says: - **Chapter 10** covers: GitHub connection, browser control, and email wiring - After connecting GitHub, you can version control your dashboard and deploy to Netlify/Vercel - **Skills ecosystem** gives your agent new abilities with one command - Browse skills at **playbooks.com** - **⚠️ Security warning:** Always read a skill's SKILL.md before installing — skills can be a vector for prompt injection --- ### 🚀 Execution Plan: | Phase | Task | Command/Action | Notes | |-------|------|----------------|-------| | **1. GitHub Integration** | Authenticate GitHub CLI | `gh auth login` | Follow prompts to authorize | | | Connect Lovable project to GitHub repo | In Lovable UI or via `gh repo create` | Enables version control for dashboard | | | Push to repo | `git push origin main` | Track all changes | | **2. Browser Control** | Enable browser tool in OpenClaw | Check if browser plugin is enabled | May need config in openclaw.json | | | Test browser access | `openclaw doctor` | Verify browser control works | | **3. Email via AgentMail** | Sign up for AgentMail | Go to agentmail.io or similar | Get API key | | | Add AgentMail API key to `.env` | `AGENTMAIL_API_KEY=xxx` | Store securely | | | Test email sending | Use skill or direct API call | Verify integration | | **4. Skills Ecosystem** | Browse available skills | Visit **playbooks.com** | Explore what's possible | | | Install a skill (example) | `npx playbooks add skill openclaw/skills --skill meeting-to-action` | Adds ability to turn meeting transcripts into action 