{"type":"message","id":"2dae9002","parentId":"cb845508","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:10:45.361Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-aeda6110bd06d145","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md — Periodic Checks\n\n---\n\n## ClawBuddy Dashboard (Step 9 Integration)\n\n- [ ] Poll for new tasks assigned to bbymama:\n  `curl -X POST \"${AGENT_COMMAND_API_URL}/functions/v1/ai-tasks\" -H \"x-webhook-secret: ${AGENT_COMMAND_WEBHOOK_SECRET}\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"action\":\"list\",\"payload\":{\"column\":\"to_do\"}}'`\n\n- [ ] Check for stale tasks (>24h in 'doing' without progress)\n\n- [ ] Log heartbeat to log_entries:\n  `{\"action\":\"log\",\"payload\":{\"message\":\"bbymama online: heartbeat check\",\"category\":\"general\",\"agent_name\":\"bbymama\",\"agent_emoji\":\"📈\"}}`\n\n- [ ] Update last_seen in agents table:\n  `{\"action\":\"status\",\"payload\":{\"agent_name\":\"bbymama\",\"status\":\"active\"}}`\n\n---\n\n## Daily\n\n- [ ] Urgent Telegram messages?\n- [ ] If quiet 8+ hours → brief check-in\n\n---\n\n## Weekly\n\n- [ ] What's Ivek working on? Aligned with goals?\n- [ ] Projects stalled? Blocked?\n- [ ] Skills practice happening?\n\n---\n\n## Push When Needed\n\n| Situation | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Avoiding important work | Call it out |\n| Scattered directions | Refocus |\n| Learning without shipping | Nudge to build |\n\n---\n\n## Response\n\n- Nothing needs attention → `HEARTBEAT_OK`\n- New task found on ClawBuddy → Pick up and execute via 8-Phase Pipeline\n- Something needs attention → reply with alert\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775545845357}}
{"type":"message","id":"2da56887","parentId":"2dae9002","timestamp":"2026-04-07T07:11:12.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now that the user authenticated GitHub successfully. Now we need to continue with Step 10: Integrations & Skills Ecosystem. We have GitHub auth done. Next steps: connect the Lovable dashboard to a GitHub repo, then set up browser control, AgentMail, and install a skill. Let's start by creating a repo for the dashboard and linking it.\n\nBut first, we need to check if there's a local project for the dashboard. The user said they deployed to Vercel via Lovable. We should connect that project to GitHub.\n\nWe can ask the user to link their Lovable project to GitHub via the Lovable UI, or we can try to clone if there's a repo already. Since we don't have direct access to Lovable, we'll guide the user.\n\nLet's respond with the next steps and ask for confirmation.\n\nWe'll also need to set up browser control and AgentMail. We'll do step by step.\n\nFirst, let's create a repo for the dashboard and link it. We'll use the GitHub CLI to create a repo and then ask the user to push their Lovable project to it or link via Lovable.\n\nWe'll also need to get the Vercel project linked to GitHub for automatic deploys.\n\nLet's proceed.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"✅ GitHub authenticated! Now let's continue **Step 10: Integrations & Skills Ecosystem**.\n\n### 📋 Next Steps:\n1. **Connect your Lovable dashboard to GitHub** (for version control & Vercel auto-deploys)\n2. **Verify browser control** in OpenClaw\n3. **Set up AgentMail** for email automation\n4. **Install your first skill** from playbooks.com\n\n---\n\n### 🔧 Step 1: Connect Dashboard to GitHub\nSince your dashboard is already on Vercel via Lovable, you need to:\n1. In Lovable UI: Go to **Project Settings → GitHub** and connect your GitHub account\n2. Or create a repo manually and push:\n   ```bash\n   # If you have the dashboard code locally:\n   git remote add origin https://github.com/ivofrankai/star-command-center-ai.git\n   git push -u origin main\n   ```\n\n**Have you already connected Lovable to GitHub, or should we create the repo now?** Once connected, Vercel will auto-deploy on pushes.\n\n---\n\n### 🌐 Step 2: Browser Control Check\nLet's verify the browser tool is working:\n```bash\nopenclaw doctor --non-interactive\n```\nWe'll check if the browser plugin is loaded and can launch a browser.\n\n---\n\n### 📧 Step 3: AgentMail Setup\n1. Sign up at [agentmail.io](https://agentmail.io) (free tier available)\n2. Get your API key\n3. Add to `.env`:\n   ```env\n   AGENTMAIL_API_KEY=your_key_here\n   ```\n4. Test with a simple send.\n\n---\n\n### ⚙️ Step 4: Install First Skill\nExample: **meeting-to-action** (turns transcripts into task lists)\n```bash\n# First, verify it's safe by reading the SKILL.md\nnpx playbooks skill openclaw/skills --skill meeting-to-action --read\n\n# Then install (only after confirming it's safe)\nnpx playbooks add skill openclaw/skills --skill meeting-to-action --confirm\n```\n\n---\n\n**What would you like to tackle first?** I can:\n- Help you create/link the GitHub repo for your dashboard\n- Run the browser control check\n- Guide you through AgentMail signup\n- Or read/install a skill together\n\nJust say the word! 🚀"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":116671,"output":782,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117453,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775545845371,"responseId":"chatcmpl-b84b3ea975891369"}}
