{"type":"message","id":"1821a153","parentId":"34324788","timestamp":"2026-04-18T17:31:16.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has been asking about voice/TTS options (free, not ElevenLabs) and I've been ignoring those requests by replying HEARTBEAT_OK. That's wrong - those are real user requests I should address. Let me respond properly to both: the voice question and the heartbeat check.\n\nActually, the current message is a heartbeat poll. But Ivek also sent \"retry\" which suggests they want me to actually respond. And earlier they asked about free TTS alternatives (not ElevenLabs) and said the voice sounds robotic.\n\nI should address the TTS question AND do the heartbeat check. But the heartbeat instruction says if nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK. However, Ivek's earlier messages about voice/TTS were being ignored - that needs attention.\n\nLet me address the voice question properly","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Ivek — sorry for ignoring your earlier questions about voice! That was wrong of me. Let me actually help.\n\n**Free TTS alternatives to ElevenLabs:**\n\n• **Piper** — fully local, open‑source, runs on your machine. Decent natural voices, zero cost\n• **Coqui TTS** — open‑source, can clone voices, runs locally\n• **Edge TTS** — uses Microsoft Edge's voices via API, completely free, very natural sounding (multi‑language incl. English)\n• **StreamElements / responsivevoice** — free tier with web‑based voices\n\n**My pick for you:** Edge TTS or Piper. Edge TTS sounds smooth and natural with zero setup. Piper is fully offline if you want privacy.\n\nWant me to set one up? 🚀"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm-5.1","usage":{"input":38725,"output":340,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39065,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776533384751,"responseId":"ch