{"type":"message","id":"a4282415","parentId":"8da0d33b","timestamp":"2026-04-19T21:46:34.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yeah! Here are your TTS options in OpenClaw — all **completely free** except ElevenLabs:\n\n**Free — no API key needed:**\n• **Microsoft (HFC voices)** — what you're using now. Lots of neural voices: `en-US-AndrewNeural`, `en-US-EricNeural`, `en-US-GuyNeural`, `en-US-ChristopherNeural`, etc.\n• Try different ones — some sound more natural than others\n\n**Free with API key:**\n• **OpenAI** — `gpt-4o-mini-tts` model, voices like Alloy, Echo, Fable, Onyx, Nova, Shimmer. Very natural and expressive. Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n• **MiniMax** — `speech-2.8-hd`, expressive voices. Needs `MINIMAX_API_KEY`\n\n**Paid:**\n• **ElevenLabs** — best quality but paid\n\n**My recommendation:** Try swapping the Microsoft voice first — there are dozens of neural voices. Some sound way more natural than the default. Want me to list the best male ones? Or if you have an OpenAI key, that's the biggest quality jump for free. 🔊"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776635194380}}
